pokedexEntries.red: Rolls down slopes to move. It rolls over any obstacle without slowing or changing its direction.
pokedexEntries.blue: Rolls down slopes to move. It rolls over any obstacle without slowing or changing its direction.
pokedexEntries.yellow: Often seen rolling down mountain trails. Obstacles are just things to roll straight over, not avoid.
pokedexEntries.gold: With a free and uncaring nature, it doesn't mind if pieces break off while it rolls down mountains.
pokedexEntries.silver: A slow walker, it rolls to move. It pays no attention to any object that happens to be in its path.
pokedexEntries.crystal: It travels by rolling on mountain paths. If it gains too much speed, it stops by running into huge rocks.
pokedexEntries.ruby: Graveler grows by feeding on rocks. Apparently, it prefers to eat rocks that are covered in moss. This Pokémon eats it way through a ton of rocks on a daily basis.
pokedexEntries.sapphire: Rocks are Graveler's favorite food. This Pokémon will climb a mountain from the base to the summit, crunchingly feasting on rocks all the while. Upon reaching the peak, it rolls back down to the bottom.
pokedexEntries.emerald: They descend from mountains by tumbling down steep slopes. They are so brutal, they smash aside obstructing trees and massive boulders with thunderous tackles.
pokedexEntries.fireRed: Be careful while hiking on mountain trails. Graveler may come rolling down the path without slowing.
pokedexEntries.leafGreen: Rolls down slopes to move. It rolls over any obstacle without slowing or changing its direction.
pokedexEntries.diamond: Graveler make their homes on sheer cliff faces by gouging out numerous horizontal holes.
pokedexEntries.pearl: It tumbles down slopes, heedless of any body parts chipping off. It eats a ton of rocks daily.
pokedexEntries.platinum: It rolls on mountain paths to move. Once it builds momentum, no Pokémon can stop it without difficulty.
pokedexEntries.heartGold: With a free and uncaring nature, it doesn't mind if pieces break off while it rolls down mountains.
pokedexEntries.soulSilver: A slow walker, it rolls to move. It pays no attention to any object that happens to be in its path.

pokedexEntries.white2: It rolls on mountain paths to move. Once it builds momentum, no Pokémon can stop it without difficulty.

pokedexEntries.y: Rolls down slopes to move. It rolls over any obstacle without slowing or changing its direction.
pokedexEntries.omegaRuby: Graveler grows by feeding on rocks. Apparently, it prefers to eat rocks that are covered in moss. This Pokémon eats its way through a ton of rocks on a daily basis.
pokedexEntries.alphaSapphire: Rocks are Graveler's favorite food. This Pokémon will climb a mountain from the base to the summit, crunchingly feasting on rocks all the while. Upon reaching the peak, it rolls back down to the bottom.
pokedexEntries.sun: Mossy rocks are its favorite food. It can devour a ton a day while crunching loudly.
pokedexEntries.moon: This slow-footed Pokémon moves by curling up and rolling instead of walking. With enough momentum, its speed can exceed 60 mph.
pokedexEntries.ultraSun: It climbs up cliffs as it heads toward the peak of a mountain. As soon as it reaches the summit, it rolls back down the way it came.
pokedexEntries.ultraMoon: It travels by rolling down cliffs. If it falls into a river, it will explode with its last gasp.
